## Perimeta for Azure {#perimeta-for-azure .oobe-Heading-2-Non-TOC}

### Overview {#overview .oobe-Heading-3-Non-TOC}

Perimeta for Azure is currently the only in-market, commoditised, highly
automated, IRAP-assessed[^1] solution geared specifically towards
meeting state and federal government customer requirements for hosting
and processing classified data up to PROTECTED in Azure.

Figure 2 \| Perimeta for Azure Overview

1. Figure 2 | Perimeta for Azure Overview
2. ![](data:image/png;base64,)


As an organisation adopts cloud services, they deploy their applications
and data into a fully software-defined environment. This environment
exists in a shared responsibility model where multiple parties are
responsible for the availability, security and integrity of the
applications and associated data. The cloud provider takes
responsibility for different layers by providing different capabilities
"as a Service (aaS)", but the configuration of those capabilities is
wholly the responsibility of the customer.

In this context the configuration of the cloud environment becomes a
critical new resource and dependency that needs to be managed and
protected. To address this requirement, oobe provides Perimeta for Azure
Deployment, Standard Support and the optional Azure Security Assessments
and Service Catalogue service to assist organisations operate
successfully and securely.

### Perimeta for Azure Deployment {#perimeta-for-azure-deployment .oobe-Heading-3-Non-TOC}

oobe will complete the Perimeta for Azure build in the identified
region/s . This includes implementing hub and spoke network
connectivity, identity and encryption boundaries, policy enforcement,
and logging and monitoring, to establish a secure framework -- enabling
rapid deployment of IaaS, PaaS and/or SaaS workloads.

oobe will build the Perimeta Hub as the dedicated central point for all
communication between the on-premises environment and Azure, and between
onboarded components within Azure. The Perimeta Hub will be configured
to leverage {//COMPANY SHORT NAME//}'s ExpressRoute or ExpressRoute
Direct connection(s) at their Data Centre or Data Centres depending on
disaster recovery requirements. Within Perimeta, oobe will either deploy
and configure Azure VPN to securely connect to {//COMPANY SHORT
NAME//}'s existing VPN termination point, or simply leverage
ExpressRoute or Express Route Direct depending on the agreed network
architecture.

### Perimeta Support {#perimeta-support .oobe-Heading-3-Non-TOC}

Perimeta for Azure provides security compliance services to ensure the
environment avoids compliance drift and maintains compliance over time.
Perimeta for Azure constantly maintains the Azure cybersecurity posture
of the organisation -- quietly maintaining compliance, enforcing
policies, monitoring the perimeter of the Azure environment, and
applying policy updates to ensure the integrity of the security
baseline.

Digital technologies and their capabilities continue to evolve, so
Perimeta for Azure support addresses the ongoing compliance of the
platform and helps guide the further secure adoption of Azure services.

The Azure Security Assessment and Service Catalogue option is a broader
service that helps guide the further secure adoption of Azure services
as an organisation expands their Azure presence. oobe's offerings in the
cybersecurity space, including ACSC 'Essential 8' compliance,
penetration and vulnerability assessments, security architectural
guidance, and monitoring and analytics capabilities work effectively to
provide all the services you need to address security compliance.

oobe's cybersecurity specialists are keeping track of the Perimeta for
Azure architecture ensuring it remains in compliance with ISM / CPS234
standards. Most importantly, oobe has direct connections into Azure
Engineering ensuring that any changes to the underlying cloud platform
are known well in advance and that policies can be configured
accordingly.

As a member of the ACSC Joint Cyber Security Centre, a partner enrolled
in the Managed Service Provider Partner Program (MSP3), and with
ISO27001 certification pending, oobe places cyber security at the core
of everything we do.

To ensure organisations can continue to confidently utilise their
Perimeta for Azure investment the most critical components of ongoing
support are included in this proposal.

This includes access to dashboards, regular reports and Perimeta for
Azure core patches and updates. These technical capabilities are
underpinned with up-to-date access to the latest security documentation,
kept 'evergreen', in lockstep with the latest guidance from the
Australian Cyber Security Centre.

## Azure Security Assessment And Service Catalogue (Optional) {#azure-security-assessment-and-service-catalogue-(optional) .oobe-Heading-2-Non-TOC}

### Azure Security Assessments (Optional) {#azure-security-assessments-(optional) .oobe-Heading-3-Non-TOC}

In addition to providing ongoing security monitoring of a customer's
existing Azure capabilities, oobe provides customers the opportunity to
identify any new Azure service they are looking to consume. oobe
provides an experienced Certified Information Systems Security
Professional (CISSP) with comprehensive Azure knowledge to undertake a
risk assessment of the requested service.

The risk assessment includes deployment of the service in an oobe lab to
practically determine any residual risks associated with key security
elements including, but not limited to, data sovereignty, system
hardening, management and monitoring, encryption and networking. In
identifying any residual risks, the oobe risk assessment also identifies
any recommended mitigation actions to consider when developing the
reference configuration of the Azure Service.

An example Azure Service Security Risk Assessment is provided at Annex
B. The Azure Service Security Risk Assessment does not provide the
reference security configuration for deployment. The risk assessment
identifies the complexity level associated with developing the Security
Configuration and customers can either develop their own configuration
or purchase the configuration from oobe.

### Azure Service Catalogue (Optional) {#azure-service-catalogue-(optional) .oobe-Heading-3-Non-TOC}

After completing the Service Assessment, oobe builds a repeatable
pattern-based Security Configuration and associated templates and
blueprints. The configuration includes all the necessary elements to
mitigate residual risks identified during the assessment phase.

The configuration is integrated into the Perimeta for Azure Virtual Data
Centre and provided for deployment in the customer's Azure Service
Catalogue. The pattern deployment is provided as either an Azure
Resource Manager template, Blueprint or via a secure deployment Standard
Operating Procedure. The complete process incorporating the Security
Assessment, Security Configuration and Service Catalogue is outlined in
Annex C Perimeta Secure Service Catalogue.

The Service Catalogue and Security Configurations are not included as
part of Standard Support.
